caption: Consistently excellent food at good prices. The meat is all fresh and yummy. Friendly staff. Hit up this local place and keep it open.

Great food but be aware that they don't accept American Express

I came here with my coworkers. I needed a light sandwich because i was due to give a presentation and i didnt want to be bogged down by a heavy meal. So I picked an egg salad sandwich. It was absolutely delicious. For such a simple sandwich, the flavors were mild but not bland, and the speed of the service was impressive, especially since we arrived during rush hour. I eyed my coworkers corned beef sandwiches throughout the meal. There were A LOT of meat in between those slices of bread! The presentation of the meal was good too. Definitely will come back when I'm in the area.

The food and service are always great. I've NEVER had a bad MEAL there. The steak and cheese or tuna sandwich are my favorites.

One of my favorite breakfast and lunch stops.  Everything is made fresh and prepared to order.  Friendly staff.  Always busy.
Good sandwiches and salads.
Breakfast sandwiches that you won't believe. The line does get long but it moves quick. It's always nice to see a place that makes their sandwiches from scratch
Fast and efficient. Perfect for lunch in a rush.

Just OK. Prices not terrible for DC, but food quality is mediocre. Two times my bagel has been terrible, had a weird “off” taste. Convenient to K Street buildings but I’d just walk to Harris Teeter next time and get a breakfast sandwich from the deli for less money. Not a fan of this one.

They don't skimp and they are nice. The portions are well sized, a good value yet not gut-busting. They serve good tasting food to hungry customers at decent prices. The place is bustling for a reason and even a longer lunch line moves super fast. There are 40+ options within 10 minutes walking or scooting, but hundreds keep coming back every lunch for a reason. You'd have to pay out the nose to get as much protein on a salad from a fast-casual chain. The lady that makes the salads is particularly sweet as is the counter and deli staff. Plenty of seating as well.
If you're in DC and you need a sandwich, just find the closest Phillip's.
Quality of the fresh food spot on! It all tatsed wonderful.  The staff were fast and friendly!

This rating is strictly for their coffee and, in particular, the Americano and House blends. I've had both the last few days and they are delicious and affordable.
Great staff.  Busy place.
Immensely popular breakfast and lunch spot.  Often long lines at peak times.  Food is good but interior layout of the restaurant is confusing and a bit chaotic especially at busy times.

Excellent option for breakfast or lunch. Sandwiches and salads made fresh to order. The muffins are baked in-house, but I don't think the sliced and wrapped cakes are. Place gets really busy during the lunch hour, so plan on a bit of a wait. Prices are not too bad for the quality of the food. This is my go-to for breakfast when I am in this area, because they always have fresh bagels and coffee.
Pricey but fresh!
Really good subs and fast service if it's not busy

Fantastic breakfast and lunch sandwiches. Everything is either made fresh right there, or brought in from somewhere fresh. You can see the quality of the ingredients as they make it right in front of you, and they use great breads, which really makes a difference. Could very well be the best sandwiches in DC.

I really like this place.  An easy walk from Union Station and where my office is.  Every morning I stop and get an outstanding blueberry muffin.  At lunch as one of their menu items they have carved meat sandwiches.  Truley wonderful.

I will not be visiting this establishment again. The cashier was rude and disrespectful.And, this place is overpriced for what they serve. The sandwiches are pretty mediocre for the price they charge. You are better off going to PotBelly, which is only a few blocks away.
Very nice staff and efficient. Geat food.  They also know their regular customers orders.  :)
Friendly staff with only a short walk to Union station.  Food is usually good but you pay DC prices.
Always a bargain here! The sandwiches are huge and freshly made.  Great  selections of bread and toppings...even cranberry sauce for your turkey sandwich!

My HSAI breakfast spot, Muah!!!

How unfortunate. At 1:30  this afternoon; Friday January 19th there were no onions, no assortment of breads or mushrooms for sandwiches. Staff apologized over and over again per each customer, but what an unfortunate situation fro them to be in. It appeared that management was not around to make a formal complaint. I asked for mayo on my friend's tuna sandwich but somehow in the staff person's scurrying there was no mayo. Of course this was only discovered after my return to the office. I really felt bad for the staff to have to continue serving people with so little resources. I hold management responsible for not stocking  their shelves. adequately. 1:30 is still too early to run out of key ingredients. Warning... don't come after 1:00 pm.

I just love this place. The sandwich ingredients are the quality you would select at home, if you could. The turkey was fantastic, and is enough for me to have for two days if I can control myself. I also tried the roast beef, which was very tender. I was going to order ham, changed my mind when I saw how good the roast beef looked (because they carve it right in front of you) and forgot what I ordered. I was pleasantly surprised that I got roast beef, and glad that I tried it.  After some time has passed after my thanksgiving turkey, I will be back for more turkey! I get it on rye with some mayo and cranberry sauce!
